The paper describes a navigation system for robotic osteotomies that uses depth images from a camera mounted on a robot arm. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. Additionally, the paper uses particle filters for pose estimation, which is a common technique in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of the system in a clinical environment, indicating that it may be relevant to the Medical Imaging (cs.MED) sub-category. Finally, the paper's focus on improving the usability of surgical robots suggests that it may be relevant to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category.
